news.title: Sand availability increases, but prices still high in Ludhiana: Builders
news.para: Ajit Singh, president of Ludhiana Builders Association said, "Ever since the public mining sites for sand became operational in the district, sand is available easily unlike in the past when there was a huge shortage."

news.title: Madras HC orders demolition of wall constructed by Olympia Tech blocking public road
news.para: The first bench of Acting Chief Justice T Raja and Justice D Bharatha Chakravarthy has also directed the authorities to restore the portion of a pond encroached by the company for its Opaline residential project and keep it open for the public.

news.title: Nagpur: Poor paying double building plan sanction fee than affluent citizens
news.para: NMC and NIT had doubled the building plan sanction charges on January 13, 2021, and June 1, 2021, respectively, with retrospective effect from July 1, 2016.

news.title: Gujarat government clears 11 town planning schemes, nine for Ahmedabad
news.para: One TP scheme each for Surat and Bhavnagar cities were also sanctioned by the government on Sunday. Two draft TP schemes and seven preliminary TP schemes for Ahmedabad have been cleared, an official statement said.

news.title: Registries pending, 300 homebuyers in Noida hold protest
news.para: The residents said the issue has been dragging on for the past six or seven years, and they will continue their protests every Sunday and sit on an indefinite hunger strike if necessary.

news.title: Delhi HC sets aside attachment of Piramal Realty's properties worth Rs 410 crore
news.para: The HC made it clear that the ED was at liberty to seek the revival of the provisional attachment orders "in accordance with law, if there is any change in the circumstances".

news.title: About 250 houses in Mainpuri receive demolition notices
news.para: Since construction work is ongoing in the area, officials pasted notices on the houses demanding an explanation for the illegal construction.

news.title: Tamil Nadu housing board collects Rs 10 lakh per month but does nothing to maintain flats
news.para: The complex does not have facilities like gym, party halls, mini-theatre or swimming pool for such high charges, they say.

news.title: Pune: Slum dwellers get multiple options for rehabilitation
news.para: The slumdwellers, whose 200 huts and 15 shops are affected by the roadwork, have now received 10 options in Kharadi, Lohegaon, Wadgaonsheri and Hadapsar for rehoming.

news.title: Madurai corporation cuts water connection to property tax defaulters
news.para: The owner of the property at Karpagam Nagar in Villapuram has not paid a total sum of 23,280 from 2015-16. Earlier, a notice was sent by the corporation to the person.

news.title: Mangaluru citizens to feel the pinch of big surge in property tax
news.para: As per an amendment, the property tax under the SAS should be calculated based on the prevailing guidance value of the property.

news.title: Reassessment of property tax from today in Patna
news.para: According to the roster, teams will cover one ward each day. PMC has urged the general public to get their properties properly assessed and pay their property tax on time.

news.title: Poor quality m-sand flooding Chennai markets
news.para: In a complaint to city police, the Tamil Nadu State Sand Lorry Owner's Association said not even 10% of the 360-odd crusher units in Chennai region work as per rules, and this has resulted in uncertified m-sand reaching all construction sites.

news.title: Over 150 plots get NOCs in special Ludhiana development body camp
news.para: ​​Over 150 NOCs were handed over here to plot holders who had applied for the same in the past.

news.title: Delhi RERA to act against builders avoiding project registration
news.para: Several builders in Delhi were avoiding project registration with the Authority despite it being compulsory for developed areas exceeding 500 square meters, irrespective of the number of apartments built on it.
